<item>
            <title>[PPLNS-7739] Create a lambda function to schedule Callminer BulkAPI export jobs</title>
                <link>https://theverygroup.atlassian.net/browse/PPLNS-7739</link>
                <project id="20015" key="PPLNS">Data Enablement</project>
                    <description>&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name="Description"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Description&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Requests to the Callminer BulkAPI don’t fetch records, they configure export jobs to run on the Callminer system and send the output to a target location. These jobs can be configured manually by anyone who has access to the TVG Callminer account, but they should ideally be configured in code and deployed from a production job.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In addition to creating and updating the scheduled export job, we will also want the ability to create one-off jobs for re-running specific time periods. These are configured the same way as scheduled jobs, but leaving the cron schedule null. The rerun mechanism should only allow the time period to be configured and should not allow the user to change any other details e.g. storage target. Any ad-hoc job that is not just a rerun can be configured manually by anyone who has access to the TVG Callminer account.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This task is to create the lambda function that will be used to configure export jobs via the BulkAPI and trigger reruns for specific time periods.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name="APIRequestDetails"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;API Request Details&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The export job can be created and updated by sending a POST (create) or PUT (update) request to the Callminer BulkAPI;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;POST /api/export/job&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Host:&lt;/em&gt; &lt;a href="https://apiuk.callminer.net/bulkexport" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;&lt;em&gt;https://apiuk.callminer.net/bulkexport&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Authorization: Bearer abc1234&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Content-Type: application/json;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;charset=utf-8&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is an example JSON payload to configure the export job;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="preformatted panel" style="border-width: 1px;"&gt;&lt;div class="preformattedContent panelContent"&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;{
    "Name": "Example Export Job",
    "Duration": {
        "SearchMode": "ClientCaptureDate",
        "LastNDays": 1,
        "LastNHours": null,
        "TimeFrame": null,
        "StartDate": null,
        "EndDate": null
    },
    "DataTypes": [
        "Category_components", "Events", “Contacts”
    ],
    "NotificationMethod": "Email",
    "EmailRecipients": [
        "Email.Address@theverygroup.com"
    ],
    "WebhookId": “Webhook ID”,
    "StorageTargetName": “Name of pre-configured storage target”,
    "Schedule": "0 30 8 ? * 4#1"
}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For a PUT request, add &lt;/p&gt;
{id}
&lt;p&gt; to the API route (the id of the job, generated after the job was created). Since this id is generated on the creation of the job, the scheduler should also incorporate a GET request to fetch the id based on the job name which is configured in code. (Note that this would mean a mechanism will be needed for updating the job name, since an updated name in code would get no results on the old name returned by the GET request).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For a GET request the below is used with no JSON payload. The id would be retrieved by searching the response for the job name.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;GET /api/export/job&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Host:&lt;/em&gt; &lt;a href="https://apiuk.callminer.net/bulkexport" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;&lt;em&gt;https://apiuk.callminer.net/bulkexport&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Authorization: Bearer abc1234&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Content-Type: application/json;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;charset=utf-8&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;Requests will need a bearer token for authorization. This is obtained by a POST request to the authorization API prior to the request to the BulkAPI. An example of an authorization request is shown below;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;POST connect/token&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Host:&lt;/em&gt; &lt;a href="https://idpuk.callminer.net" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;&lt;em&gt;https://idpuk.callminer.net&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Json payload;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="preformatted panel" style="border-width: 1px;"&gt;&lt;div class="preformattedContent panelContent"&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;{
  "client_id": "abcd-1234",
  "client_secret": "abcd-1234",
  "grant_type": "client_credentials",
  "scope": "https://callminer.net/auth/platform-bulkexport"
}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
